// ── Helper: b_str2int ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

/// Parse an integer in an arbitrary base from the byte slice `s`.
///
/// Returns `Some((consumed, value))` on success, where `consumed` is the number
/// of bytes from the start of `s` that were processed (leading and trailing
